      "writtenOn": "2020-09-10T18:22:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "At first I was convinced that you were right here, but then I realized--what about `continue`? The continue statement needs to evaluate the whole test-expression. So hypothetically we only perform the inlining in a do-while loop that lacks continues.\n\nSame thing with `for` loops as well--if you don\u0027t use `continue`, a for loop could inline its test at the top and its increment at the bottom. Same for `while`.",
